cs.DC, cs.CE, cs.AR, cs.NI, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper focuses on building clusters using Single Board Computers (SBCs) for a small scale data center and evaluating their performance and energy efficiency using popular benchmarks. This category is the most likely fit for this paper.
2. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper discusses the cost of operating SBC-based clusters by correlating energy utilization for the execution time of various benchmarks using workloads of different sizes. This category is also a likely fit as it deals with the computational aspects of engineering and science.
3. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper utilizes Single Board Computers (SBCs) for building clusters, which falls under the hardware architecture domain. This category is a possible fit.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper evaluates the network throughput of the SBC-based clusters, which falls under the networking domain. This category is also a possible fit.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the effectiveness of SBC-based clusters as a testbed for inexpensive and green cloud computing research, which falls under the systems and control domain. This category is a less likely fit but still possible.
